Pennsylvania ’s law requiring voters
to show photo ID at the polls is troublesome because state
workers are poorly trained on the measure’s requirements and are
unprepared for questions about the process of acquiring an
alternative voting-only identification, voters and activists
testified.  To contact the reporter on this story:
